',{id:"solar_capacity_growth_by_state_2015_2025",title:"Utility-scale solar capacity growth by state 2015-2025 - the fastest energy deployment in US history",sub:"Texas: grew from 0.5 GW solar in 2015 to 37.4 GW in 2025 - the largest solar fleet in the US. California: 22.6 GW. The solar deployment rate has exceeded any prior US energy buildout including the gas boom. Texas alone added more solar in 2024 than the entire US solar fleet in 2019.",type:"MAP",geo:"us_state",fmt:"State choropleth",tbl:"EIA Electric Power Monthly state solar capacity 2015-2025 (public monthly)",section:"Energy",ext:["ACS 5-year estimates: MHI, poverty rate, population by geography (Census API - free, tidycensus)","BEA Regional: GDP + personal income per capita by state (apps.bea.gov - free)","Census Population Estimates: annual population by state/county (census.gov - free)","EIA State Energy Data System: production + consumption by state (eia.gov - free API)"],vars:["renewable_energy_share","energy_consumption_per_capita"],join:["coal_consumption","rep_pct","manufacturing_employment_trend"],sc:{emotional:7,relatability:6,surprise:8,tension:5,visual:7,data_ready:9,originality:6},vs:68,tags:"solar capacity growth state 2015 2025 Texas 0.5 37.4 GW California 22.6 fastest energy deployment US history 2024 added more entire 2019 fleet EIA Electric Power Monthly"}',
