',{id:"xref_carbon_price_vs_emission_reduction_country",title:"Carbon price vs. emission reduction achieved by country - does pricing carbon work?",sub:"Sweden: $137/ton CO2 carbon price, 39% emissions reduction since 1990. EU ETS: $65/ton average, 16% reduction. Australia carbon tax (repealed 2014): achieved 1.4% reduction in 2 years before repeal. USA no national carbon price: 22% reduction driven by gas-coal switching and efficiency. The data supports pricing but the counterfactual is contested.",type:"XREF",geo:"worldwide",fmt:"Scatter plot",tbl:"World Bank Carbon Pricing Dashboard + IEA emissions by country (both public)",section:"Energy",ext:["World Bank Open Data: GDP, population, income by country (data.worldbank.org - free API)"],vars:["renewable_energy_share","energy_consumption_per_capita"],join:["rd_pct_gdp","trade_balance_goods","net_migration_rate"],sc:{emotional:7,relatability:5,surprise:7,tension:6,visual:5,data_ready:7,originality:7},vs:60,tags:"carbon price emission reduction country Sweden $137 39% EU $65 16% Australia repealed 1.4% USA no price 22% gas-coal counterfactual contested World Bank Carbon Pricing IEA"}',
',{id:"xref_wind_energy_county_vs_property_tax",title:"Wind energy capacity by county vs. property tax revenue gained - who benefits from wind",sub:"Holt County NE: $41M in annual property tax revenue from wind turbines on 380K acres - transforming rural county budgets. Sherman County TX: $67M. Wind energy property taxes fund rural schools in counties that were losing population. The wind tax map is the rural fiscal salvation map.",type:"XREF",geo:"us_county",fmt:"County choropleth",tbl:"AWEA wind energy installations + state property tax data by county (public)",section:"Energy",ext:["ACS 5-year estimates: MHI, poverty rate, population by geography (Census API - free, tidycensus)","Census Population Estimates: annual population by state/county (census.gov - free)","BLS LAUS: unemployment + labor force by county (bls.gov - free)","EIA State Energy Data System: production + consumption by state (eia.gov - free API)"],vars:["renewable_energy_share","rural_population_pct"],join:["state_local_revenue_per_capita","median_household_income","expenditure_per_pupil"],sc:{emotional:7,relatability:6,surprise:8,tension:3,visual:6,data_ready:6,originality:8},vs:63,tags:"wind energy county property tax Holt NE $41M Sherman TX $67M rural schools losing population fiscal salvation map AWEA installations state property tax rural budget transformation"}',
